---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/content.css';
---
<BaseLayout title="Medical Equipment Planning: Estrelis vs Spreadsheets | Estrelis.ai" description="Compare Estrelis.ai to spreadsheet-based medical equipment planning. See why healthcare teams switch from Excel to purpose-built MEQ planning software with AI, Revit sync, and procurement tools.">

  <section class="content-hero">
    <h1>Estrelis vs. Spreadsheets</h1>
    <p>Most healthcare equipment planning still happens in spreadsheets. Here's why teams are switching to purpose-built software.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <table class="compare-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Capability</th>
          <th>Spreadsheets</th>
          <th>Estrelis</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Equipment Catalog</td>
          <td>Manual lookups across files</td>
          <td>Centralized AI-powered catalog with 295K+ items</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Spec Matching</td>
          <td>Copy-paste from vendor sheets</td>
          <td>AI matches specs automatically with confidence scores</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Budget Tracking</td>
          <td>Manual formulas, version confusion</td>
          <td>Real-time rollups by department, building, phase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Revit Integration</td>
          <td>Manual export/import of room lists</td>
          <td>Two-way sync via desktop plugin</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Multi-User Collaboration</td>
          <td>File locking, merge conflicts</td>
          <td>Real-time multi-user with role-based access</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Procurement</td>
          <td>Separate emails and documents</td>
          <td>RFQ generation, quote comparison, PO creation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Client Review</td>
          <td>Email PDF attachments</td>
          <td>Secure client portal with magic link access</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Discontinued Items</td>
          <td>Discovered at procurement</td>
          <td>AI flags end-of-life items proactively</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Field Inventory</td>
          <td>Paper forms, manual entry</td>
          <td>iPad with 360° photos and barcode scanning</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Audit Trail</td>
          <td>No history of changes</td>
          <td>Full change tracking and version history</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>The Real Cost of Spreadsheets</h2>
    <p>Spreadsheet-based planning doesn't just slow teams down — it introduces errors that compound across large projects. A mismatched catalog item, an outdated price, or a missed discontinued product can cascade into change orders, procurement delays, and budget overruns that cost far more than the planning tool itself.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Version control issues lead to duplicate or conflicting equipment lists</li>
      <li>Manual catalog lookups consume hours per project</li>
      <li>Discontinued items discovered too late in procurement</li>
      <li>Budget reconciliation requires days of manual formula checking</li>
      <li>No audit trail when stakeholders question planning decisions</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Ready to move beyond spreadsheets?</h2>
    <p>See how Estrelis replaces manual processes with intelligent automation.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary btn-lg">Request a Demo</a>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
